When I was a Mormon missionary we were not allowed to study kanji, as it was
considered a distraction from our real work there. (Some people just got too
into the kanji, and forgot to study things that were relatively more
important.)

I could not imagine trying to read romanized Japanese -- too many
homophones. I get very confused when trying to read hiragana sometimes,
without the kanji to direct the meanings. I am ashamed to admit that I have
the opposite problem though-- sometimes I don't know how the kanji are
pronounced, even for some very common words, and I find myself reaching for
familiar words in conversation, only to discover that I don't know how to
pronounce them!

Warren

