To take this concept of kanji-illiterate translators to its extreme,
we can ask,
(1) Can a blind person be an interpreter?
(1a) Can born-sighted blind person be an interpreter?
(1b) Can a born-blind blind person be an interpreter?
(2) Can a blind person be a translator?
(2a) Can born-sighted blind person be a translator?
(2b) Can a born-blind blind person be a translator?

It seems to me that the answer for (1) is Yes in both cases,
and for (2) is Yes in both cases, given some visual-to-aural
or text-to-Braille system.
